 the git repository root |\\n  3191→+| `ENTIRE_PROTOCOL_VERSION` | Protocol version (`1`) |\\n  3192→+\\n  3193→+The working directory is set to the repository root.\\n  3194→+\\n  3195→+## Communication Model\\n  3196→+\\n  3197→+- **Subcommand-based:** Each Agent interface method maps to a CLI subcommand.\\n  3198→+- **JSON over stdin/stdout:** Structured data uses JSON. Transcripts use raw bytes.\\n  3199→+- **Stateless:** Each invocation is independent — no persistent connection.\\n  3200→+- **Exit codes:** `0` = success, non-zero = error. Error messages go to stderr.\\n  3201→+\\n  3202→+## Subcommands\\n  3203→+\\n  3204→+### Always Required\\n  3205→+\\n  3206→+#### `info`\\n  3207→+\\n  3208→+Returns agent metadata and declared capabilities.\\n  3209→+\\n  3210→+**Arguments:** None\\n  3211→+\\n  3212→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3213→+\\n  3214→+```json\\n  3215→+{\\n  3216→+  \\\"protocol_version\\\": 1,\\n  3217→+  \\\"name\\\": \\\"cursor\\\",\\n  3218→+  \\\"type\\\": \\\"Cursor\\\",\\n  3219→+  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Cursor - AI-powered code editor\\\",\\n  3220→+  \\\"is_preview\\\": true,\\n  3221→+  \\\"protected_dirs\\\": [\\\".cursor\\\"],\\n  3222→+  \\\"hook_names\\\": [\\\"session-start\\\", \\\"session-end\\\", \\\"stop\\\"],\\n  3223→+  \\\"capabilities\\\": {\\n  3224→+    \\\"hooks\\\": true,\\n  3225→+    \\\"transcript_analyzer\\\": true,\\n  3226→+    \\\"transcript_preparer\\\": false,\\n  3227→+    \\\"token_calculator\\\": false,\\n  3228→+    \\\"text_generator\\\": false,\\n  3229→+    \\\"hook_response_writer\\\": false,\\n  3230→+    \\\"subagent_aware_extractor\\\": false\\n  3231→+  }\\n  3232→+}\\n  3233→+```\\n  3234→+\\n  3235→+The `capabilities` object determines which optional subcommands the CLI will call. If a capability is `false` or missing, the CLI will never invoke the corresponding subcommands.\\n  3236→+\\n  3237→+#### `detect`\\n  3238→+\\n  3239→+Checks whether the agent is present/usable in the current environment.\\n  3240→+\\n  3241→+**Arguments:** None\\n  3242→+\\n  3243→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3244→+\\n  3245→+```json\\n  3246→+{\\\"present\\\": true}\\n  3247→+```\\n  3248→+\\n  3249→+#### `get-session-id`\\n  3250→+\\n  3251→+Extracts the session ID from a hook input event.\\n  3252→+\\n  3253→+**Input (stdin):** JSON — the [HookInput object](#hookinput-object)\\n  3254→+\\n  3255→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3256→+\\n  3257→+```json\\n  3258→+{\\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\"}\\n  3259→+```\\n  3260→+\\n  3261→+#### `get-session-dir --repo-path <path>`\\n  3262→+\\n  3263→+Returns the directory where agent sessions are stored.\\n  3264→+\\n  3265→+**Arguments:**\\n  3266→+- `--repo-path` — Absolute path to the repository\\n  3267→+\\n  3268→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3269→+\\n  3270→+```json\\n  3271→+{\\\"session_dir\\\": \\\"/path/to/sessions\\\"}\\n  3272→+```\\n  3273→+\\n  3274→+#### `resolve-session-file --session-dir <dir> --session-id <id>`\\n  3275→+\\n  3276→+Resolves the session file path from a session directory and ID.\\n  3277→+\\n  3278→+**Arguments:**\\n  3279→+- `--session-dir` — Session directory path\\n  3280→+- `--session-id` — Session identifier\\n  3281→+\\n  3282→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3283→+\\n  3284→+```json\\n  3285→+{\\\"session_file\\\": \\\"/path/to/session/file.jsonl\\\"}\\n  3286→+```\\n  3287→+\\n  3288→+#### `read-session`\\n  3289→+\\n  3290→+Reads session data from a hook input event.\\n  3291→+\\n  3292→+**Input (stdin):** JSON — the [HookInput object](#hookinput-object)\\n  3293→+\\n  3294→+**Output (stdout):** JSON — [AgentSession object](#agentsession-object)\\n  3295→+\\n  3296→+```json\\n  3297→+{\\n  3298→+  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n  3299→+  \\\"agent_name\\\": \\\"cursor\\\",\\n  3300→+  \\\"repo_path\\\": \\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\n  3301→+  \\\"session_ref\\\": \\\"/path/to/file.jsonl\\\",\\n  3302→+  \\\"start_time\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\",\\n  3303→+  \\\"native_data\\\": null,\\n  3304→+  \\\"modified_files\\\": [\\\"src/main.go\\\"],\\n  3305→+  \\\"new_files\\\": [],\\n  3306→+  \\\"deleted_files\\\": []\\n  3307→+}\\n  3308→+```\\n  3309→+\\n  3310→+#### `write-session`\\n  3311→+\\n  3312→+Writes/updates session data.\\n  3313→+\\n  3314→+**Input (stdin):** JSON — the [AgentSession object](#agentsession-object)\\n  3315→+\\n  3316→+**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n  3317→+\\n  3318→+#### `read-transcript --session-ref <path>`\\n  3319→+\\n  3320→+Reads a transcript file and returns its raw bytes.\\n  3321→+\\n  3322→+**Arguments:**\\n  3323→+- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n  3324→+\\n  3325→+**Output (stdout):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n  3326→+\\n  3327→+#### `chunk-transcript --max-size <n>`\\n  3328→+\\n  3329→+Splits a transcript into chunks for storage.\\n  3330→+\\n  3331→+**Input (stdin):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n  3332→+\\n  3333→+**Arguments:**\\n  3334→+- `--max-size` — Maximum chunk size in bytes\\n  3335→+\\n  3336→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3337→+\\n  3338→+```json\\n  3339→+{\\\"chunks\\\": [\\\"<base64-encoded-chunk>\\\", \\\"...\\\"]}\\n  3340→+```\\n  3341→+\\n  3342→+#### `reassemble-transcript`\\n  3343→+\\n  3344→+Reassembles transcript chunks back into a full transcript.\\n  3345→+\\n  3346→+**Input (stdin):** JSON\\n  3347→+\\n  3348→+```json\\n  3349→+{\\\"chunks\\\": [\\\"<base64-encoded-chunk>\\\", \\\"...\\\"]}\\n  3350→+```\\n  3351→+\\n  3352→+**Output (stdout):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n  3353→+\\n  3354→+#### `format-resume-command --session-id <id>`\\n  3355→+\\n  3356→+Returns the command a user can run to resume a session.\\n  3357→+\\n  3358→+**Arguments:**\\n  3359→+- `--session-id` — Session identifier\\n  3360→+\\n  3361→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3362→+\\n  3363→+```json\\n  3364→+{\\\"command\\\": \\\"cursor --resume abc123\\\"}\\n  3365→+```\\n  3366→+\\n  3367→+### Capability: `hooks`\\n  3368→+\\n  3369→+These subcommands are required when `capabilities.hooks` is `true`.\\n  3370→+\\n  3371→+#### `parse-hook --hook <name>`\\n  3372→+\\n  3373→+Parses a raw agent hook payload into a structured event.\\n  3374→+\\n  3375→+**Arguments:**\\n  3376→+- `--hook` — Hook name (e.g., \\\"stop\\\", \\\"session-start\\\")\\n  3377→+\\n  3378→+**Input (stdin):** Raw agent hook payload bytes.\\n  3379→+\\n  3380→+**Output (stdout):** JSON — the parsed [Event object](#event-object), or `null` if the payload is not relevant.\\n  3381→+\\n  3382→+#### `install-hooks [--local-dev] [--force]`\\n  3383→+\\n  3384→+Installs agent hooks for Entire integration.\\n  3385→+\\n  3386→+**Arguments:**\\n  3387→+- `--local-dev` — Use local development binary path (optional)\\n  3388→+- `--force` — Overwrite existing hooks (optional)\\n  3389→+\\n  3390→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3391→+\\n  3392→+```json\\n  3393→+{\\\"hooks_installed\\\": 3}\\n  3394→+```\\n  3395→+\\n  3396→+#### `uninstall-hooks`\\n  3397→+\\n  3398→+Removes installed agent hooks.\\n  3399→+\\n  3400→+**Arguments:** None\\n  3401→+\\n  3402→+**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n  3403→+\\n  3404→+#### `are-hooks-installed`\\n  3405→+\\n  3406→+Checks whether hooks are currently installed.\\n  3407→+\\n  3408→+**Arguments:** None\\n  3409→+\\n  3410→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3411→+\\n  3412→+```json\\n  3413→+{\\\"installed\\\": true}\\n  3414→+```\\n  3415→+\\n  3416→+### Capability: `transcript_analyzer`\\n  3417→+\\n  3418→+Required when `capabilities.transcript_analyzer` is `true`.\\n  3419→+\\n  3420→+#### `get-transcript-position --path <path>`\\n  3421→+\\n  3422→+Returns the current byte position/size of a transcript file.\\n  3423→+\\n  3424→+**Arguments:**\\n  3425→+- `--path` — Path to the transcript file\\n  3426→+\\n  3427→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3428→+\\n  3429→+```json\\n  3430→+{\\\"position\\\": 12345}\\n  3431→+```\\n  3432→+\\n  3433→+#### `extract-modified-files --path <path> --offset <n>`\\n  3434→+\\n  3435→+Extracts the list of files modified by the