3492→+\\n  3493→+#### `calculate-tokens --offset <n>`\\n  3494→+\\n  3495→+Calculates token usage from a transcript.\\n  3496→+\\n  3497→+**Input (stdin):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n  3498→+\\n  3499→+**Arguments:**\\n  3500→+- `--offset` — Byte offset to start calculating from\\n  3501→+\\n  3502→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3503→+\\n  3504→+```json\\n  3505→+{\\n  3506→+  \\\"input_tokens\\\": 1500,\\n  3507→+  \\\"cache_creation_tokens\\\": 0,\\n  3508→+  \\\"cache_read_tokens\\\": 200,\\n  3509→+  \\\"output_tokens\\\": 500,\\n  3510→+  \\\"api_call_count\\\": 3,\\n  3511→+  \\\"subagent_tokens\\\": null\\n  3512→+}\\n  3513→+```\\n  3514→+\\n  3515→+Only `input_tokens` and `output_tokens` are required. The optional fields (`cache_creation_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, `api_call_count`) default to `0` if omitted. `subagent_tokens` is an optional nested object with the same structure, for agents that spawn subagents.\\n  3516→+\\n  3517→+### Capability: `text_generator`\\n  3518→+\\n  3519→+Required when `capabilities.text_generator` is `true`.\\n  3520→+\\n  3521→+#### `generate-text --model <model>`\\n  3522→+\\n  3523→+Generates text using the agent's underlying LLM.\\n  3524→+\\n  3525→+**Input (stdin):** Prompt text.\\n  3526→+\\n  3527→+**Arguments:**\\n  3528→+- `--model` — Model to use for generation\\n  3529→+\\n  3530→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3531→+\\n  3532→+```json\\n  3533→+{\\\"text\\\": \\\"Generated response text\\\"}\\n  3534→+```\\n  3535→+\\n  3536→+### Capability: `hook_response_writer`\\n  3537→+\\n  3538→+Required when `capabilities.hook_response_writer` is `true`.\\n  3539→+\\n  3540→+#### `write-hook-response --message <message>`\\n  3541→+\\n  3542→+Writes a message in the agent's native hook response format.\\n  3543→+\\n  3544→+**Arguments:**\\n  3545→+- `--message` — Message to write\\n  3546→+\\n  3547→+**Output (stdout):** Agent-native format bytes (e.g., JSONL for Claude Code).\\n  3548→+\\n  3549→+### Capability: `subagent_aware_extractor`\\n  3550→+\\n  3551→+Required when `capabilities.subagent_aware_extractor` is `true`.\\n  3552→+\\n  3553→+#### `extract-all-modified-files --offset <n> --subagents-dir <dir>`\\n  3554→+\\n  3555→+Extracts modified files from both the main transcript and any subagent transcripts.\\n  3556→+\\n  3557→+**Input (stdin):** Raw main transcript bytes.\\n  3558→+\\n  3559→+**Arguments:**\\n  3560→+- `--offset` — Byte offset for the main transcript\\n  3561→+- `--subagents-dir` — Directory containing subagent transcripts\\n  3562→+\\n  3563→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3564→+\\n  3565→+```json\\n  3566→+{\\\"files\\\": [\\\"file1.go\\\", \\\"file2.go\\\"]}\\n  3567→+```\\n  3568→+\\n  3569→+#### `calculate-total-tokens --offset <n> --subagents-dir <dir>`\\n  3570→+\\n  3571→+Calculates total token usage across main transcript and subagent transcripts.\\n  3572→+\\n  3573→+**Input (stdin):** Raw main transcript bytes.\\n  3574→+\\n  3575→+**Arguments:**\\n  3576→+- `--offset` — Byte offset for the main transcript\\n  3577→+- `--subagents-dir` — Directory containing subagent transcripts\\n  3578→+\\n  3579→+**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n  3580→+\\n  3581→+```json\\n  3582→+{\\n  3583→+  \\\"input_tokens\\\": 5000,\\n  3584→+  \\\"cache_creation_tokens\\\": 0,\\n  3585→+  \\\"cache_read_tokens\\\": 1000,\\n  3586→+  \\\"output_tokens\\\": 2000,\\n  3587→+  \\\"api_call_count\\\": 8,\\n  3588→+  \\\"subagent_tokens\\\": {\\n  3589→+    \\\"input_tokens\\\": 2000,\\n  3590→+    \\\"output_tokens\\\": 800\\n  3591→+  }\\n  3592→+}\\n  3593→+```\\n  3594→+\\n  3595→+Same token usage format as `calculate-tokens`. The `subagent_tokens` field aggregates usage from all subagents.\\n  3596→+\\n  3597→+## Shared Object Definitions\\n  3598→+\\n  3599→+### HookInput Object\\n  3600→+\\n  3601→+The HookInput object is passed via stdin to `get-session-id` and `read-session`.\\n  3602→+\\n  3603→+```json\\n  3604→+{\\n  3605→+  \\\"hook_type\\\": \\\"stop\\\",\\n  3606→+  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n  3607→+  \\\"session_ref\\\": \\\"/path/to/transcript.jsonl\\\",\\n  3608→+  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\",\\n  3609→+  \\\"user_prompt\\\": \\\"Fix the login bug\\\",\\n  3610→+  \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"Write\\\",\\n  3611→+  \\\"tool_use_id\\\": \\\"toolu_abc123\\\",\\n  3612→+  \\\"tool_input\\\": {\\\"path\\\": \\\"/src/main.go\\\"},\\n  3613→+  \\\"raw_data\\\": {\\\"custom_field\\\": \\\"value\\\"}\\n  3614→+}\\n  3615→+```\\n  3616→+\\n  3617→+| Field | Type | Description |\\n  3618→+|---|---|---|\\n  3619→+| `hook_type` | string | Hook type: `session_start`, `session_end`, `user_prompt_submit`, `stop`, `pre_tool_use`, `post_tool_use` |\\n  3620→+| `session_id` | string | Agent session identifier |\\n  3621→+| `session_ref` | string | Agent-specific session reference (typically a file path) |\\n  3622→+| `timestamp` | string | RFC 3339 timestamp |\\n  3623→+| `user_prompt` | string | User's prompt text (from `user_prompt_submit` hooks). Optional. |\\n  3624→+| `tool_name` | string | Tool name (from `pre_tool_use`/`post_tool_use` hooks). Optional. |\\n  3625→+| `tool_use_id` | string | Tool invocation ID. Optional. |\\n  3626→+| `tool_input` | object | Raw tool input JSON. Optional. |\\n  3627→+| `raw_data` | object | Agent-specific data for extension. Optional. |\\n  3628→+\\n  3629→+### AgentSession Object\\n  3630→+\\n  3631→+Used as input to `write-session` and output from `read-session`.\\n  3632→+\\n  3633→+```json\\n  3634→+{\\n  3635→+  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n  3636→+  \\\"agent_name\\\": \\\"cursor\\\",\\n  3637→+  \\\"repo_path\\\": \\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\n  3638→+  \\\"session_ref\\\": \\\"/path/to/transcript.jsonl\\\",\\n  3639→+  \\\"start_time\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\",\\n  3640→+  \\\"native_data\\\": null,\\n  3641→+  \\\"modified_files\\\": [\\\"src/main.go\\\"],\\n  3642→+  \\\"new_files\\\": [\\\"src/new_file.go\\\"],\\n  3643→+  \\\"deleted_files\\\": []\\n  3644→+}\\n  3645→+```\\n  3646→+\\n  3647→+| Field | Type | Description |\\n  3648→+|---|---|---|\\n  3649→+| `session_id` | string | Agent session identifier |\\n  3650→+| `agent_name` | string | Agent registry name |\\n  3651→+| `repo_path` | string | Absolute path to the repository |\\n  3652→+| `session_ref` | string | Path/reference to session in agent's storage |\\n  3653→+| `start_time` | string | RFC 3339 timestamp of session start |\\n  3654→+| `native_data` | bytes/null | Session content in agent's native format (opaque to CLI) |\\n  3655→+| `modified_files` | string[] | Files modified during the session |\\n  3656→+| `new_files` | string[] | Files created during the session |\\n  3657→+| `deleted_files` | string[] | Files deleted during the session |\\n  3658→+\\n  3659→+### Event Object\\n  3660→+\\n  3661→+Returned by `parse-hook`. Represents a normalized lifecycle event.\\n  3662→+\\n  3663→+```json\\n  3664→+{\\n  3665→+  \\\"type\\\": 3,\\n  3666→+  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n  3667→+  \\\"session_ref\\\": \\\"/path/to/transcript.jsonl\\\",\\n  3668→+  \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Fix the login bug\\\",\\n  3669→+  \\\"model\\\": \\\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\\\",\\n  3670→+  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\"\\n  3671→+}\\n  3672→+```\\n  3673→+\\n  3674→+| Field | Type | Description |\\n  3675→+|---|---|---|\\n  3676→+| `type` | int | **Required.** Event type (see table below) |\\n  3677→+| `session_id` | string | **Required.** Agent session identifier |\\n  3678→+| `previous_session_id` | string | Non-empty when this event represents a session continuation/handoff. Optional. |\\n  3679→+| `session_ref` | string | Agent-specific transcript reference. Optional. |\\n  3680→+| `prompt` | string | User's prompt text (on `TurnStart` events). Optional. |\\n  3681→+| `model` | string | LLM model identifier. Optional. |\\n  3682→+| `timestamp` | string | RFC 3339 timestamp. Optional. |\\n  3683→+| `tool_use_id` | string | Tool invocation ID (for `SubagentStart`/`SubagentEnd`). Optional. |\\n  3684→+| `subagent_id` | string | Subagent instance ID (for `SubagentEnd`). Optional. |\\n  3685→+| `tool_input` | object | Raw tool input JSON (for subagent type/description extraction). Optional. |\\n  3686→+| `subagent_type` | string | Kind of subagent (for `SubagentStart`/`SubagentEnd`). Optional. |\\n  3687→+| `task_description` | string | Subagent task description. Optional. |\\n  3688→+| `response_message` | string | Message to display to the user via the agent. Optional. |\\n  3689→+| `metadata` | object | Agent-specific state preserved across events. Optional. |\\n  3690→+\\n  3691→+**Event types:**\\n  3692→+\\n  3693→+| Value | Name | Description |\\n  3694→+|---|---|---|\\n  3695→+| 1 | SessionStart | Agent session has begun |\\n  3696→+| 2 | TurnStart | User submitted a prompt, agent is about to work |\\n  3697→+| 3 | TurnEnd | Agent finished responding to a prompt |\\n  3698→+| 4 | Compaction | Agent is compressing its context window (triggers save + offset reset) |\\n  3699→+| 5 | SessionEnd | Session has been terminated |\\n  3700→+| 6 | SubagentStart | A subagent (task) has been spawned |\\n  3701→+| 7 | SubagentEnd | A subagent (task) has completed |\\n  3702→+\\n  3703→+## Error Handling\\n  3704→+\\n  3705→+- Exit code `0` indicates success.\\n  3706→+- Any non-zero exit code indicates an error.\\n  3707→+- Error messages should be written to stderr.\\n  3708→+- The CLI captures stderr and wraps it in a Go error.\\n  3709→+- If the binary is not found in PATH, the agent is simply not registered.\\n  3710→+- If `info` fails or returns invalid JSON, the binary is skipped during discovery.\\n  3711→+\\n  3712→+## Versioning\\n  3713→+\\n  3714→+The protocol version is declared in the `info` response (`protocol_version` field) and set via `ENTIRE_PROTOCOL_VERSION` environment variable. The CLI checks that the binary's protocol version matches its expected version before registering the agent.\\n  3715→+\\